2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new measure that uses semantic symbolic structure to evaluate GEC output, which is a common area of research in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper may involve the use of machine learning techniques to develop and evaluate the proposed measure. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as neural networks are commonly used in GEC research and the paper may involve the use of neural networks to develop and evaluate the proposed measure. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve the use of sound-based techniques to evaluate the proposed measure.
